<table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4"><tr bgcolor="#000000"><td><font color="#FFFFFF"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial" size="6">Orothe Control</font></td></tr></table><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td></td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Author</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Ryan</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Description</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Commonly called a mother-may-I deck, this deck is made to control everything that happens in play.  I&#39;ve always played this type of deck and this is my most recent version.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Cards</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Magi:<br>
<!--448-->O&#39;Qua (starts <!--459-->Submerge)<br>
<br>
<!--626-->Voda (usually interchanged to, but starts <!--459-->Submerge and <!--621-->Reef Hyren)<br>
<br>
<!--625-->Quilla (starts the <!--627-->Hubdra&#39;s Cube)<br>
<br>
Creatures: 22<br>
3x <!--434}<!--{516-->Giant <!--766-->Parathin<br>
3x <!--621-->Reef Hyren<br>
3x <!--763-->Deep <!--443-->Wellisk<br>
3x <!--441-->Sea Barl<br>
3x <!--443-->Wellisk<br>
3x <!--764-->Iximin<br>
2x <!--429-->Abaquist<br>
1x <!--433-->Deep Hyren<br>
1x <!--618-->Hunter Jile<br>
<br>
Spells: 12<br>
3x <!--460-->Tidal Wave<br>
3x <!--462-->Undertow<br>
3x <!--498-->Thunderquake<br>
1x <!--459-->Submerge<br>
1x <!--790-->Beam of Light<br>
1x <!--772-->Shell<br>
<br>
Relics: 6<br>
3x <!--652-->Rayje&#39;s Belt<br>
2x <!--789-->Tomorrow&#39;s Jewel<br>
1x <!--627-->Hubdra&#39;s Cube  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">O&#39;Qua leads off because she establishes control.  Normally, if I go first, I get a Reef Hyren and start rebuking.  If I go second, I&#39;ll normally get one of four things: Abaquist, Deep Hyren, Hunter Jile, or Sea Barl.  The Abaquist is obviously for taking something over w/ 6 or less energy.  The Deep Hyren is for swarms.  Just conjure, submerge, and Hurricane away.  The Hunter Jile is for Corrupt.  The Sea Barl I rarely Conjure for, but I will if there is something in play that MUST be killed, and I have no removal for it in my hand.<br>
<br>
Voda is a beat stick.  And w/ 3 copies of things like Iximin, Thunderquake, Undertow, and Tidal Wave, you should never lose control of him.  Suicide him before you lose control if necessary.  Deep Wellisk is awesome w/ Voda if it&#39;s the largest creature in play.  So if you haven&#39;t used the sumberge from O&#39;Qua, it&#39;s worth investing in a Deep Wellisk.  Don&#39;t fret losing Voda, though, when playing against a good player, he should go the distance, but will likely die.<br>
<br>
Quilla is a beating as well.  Her energize 7 lets you play the removal spells or whatever you want.  As long as she has a halfway decent hand when she comes up, she should be able to cut through a magi or two.<br>
<br>
Remember, don&#39;t get too eager to kill magi.  If you can keep the current magi in check, but can&#39;t keep control when the next magi shows up w/ lots of energy, then don&#39;t kill their magi.  Wait to build up.  Between Voda&#39;s Deluge and Quilla&#39;s energize 7, nobody should be able to pull a reverse on you if you start toying w/ them.<br>
<br>
Ryan Anderson<br>
Orothe Player for Life </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
